 internal density. A\nwide range of particle sizes, from mm to 10 m, concentrate in the turbulent gas\nflow. Overdense filaments fragment gravitationally into bound particle clumps,\nwith most mass entering planetesimals of contracted radii from 100 to 500 km,\ndepending on local disc properties. We propose a hybrid model for planetesimal\nformation where particle growth starts unaided by self-gravity but later\nproceeds inside gravitationally collapsing pebble clumps to form planetesimals\nwith a wide range of sizes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 6 Feb 2014 13:15:32 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 10 Dec 2014 11:40:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-18"}
